-- Fidelity National Boosts Cash Part of LPS Deal by $500 Million
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r
-- 2013-06-19T22:02:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-19/fidelity-national-boosts-cash-part-of-lps-deal-by-500-million.html
Fidelity National Financial Inc.,
the largest U.S. title insurer, said it will boost the cash
portion of the payment for  Lender Processing Services Inc. (LPS)  by
$500 million.  The value of the deal remains about $2.9 billion, with two-thirds of the sum now coming in cash and the rest in Fidelity
National stock, the Jacksonville, Florida-based insurer said
today in a statement distributed by PR Newswire.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zachary Tracer in  New York  at 
